SIMPLE: emergent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emergent
<hw>E*mer"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emergens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>emergere</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Rising or emerging out of a fluid or anything that covers or
conceals; issuing; coming to light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mountains huge appear <qex>emergent</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suddenly appearing; arising unexpectedly; calling
for prompt action; urgent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Protection granted in <qex>emergent</qex> danger.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Emergent year</b></col> <fld>(Chron.)</fld>, <cd>the
epoch or date from which any people begin to compute their time or
dates; as, the <xex>emergent year</xex> of Christendom is that of the
birth of Christ; the <xex>emergent year</xex> of the United States is
that of the declaration of their independence.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>E*mer"gent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>E*mer"gent*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[R.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emeril</ent>⟦br⟧
